{"word":"H7211 - רְאָיָה - Rᵉʼâyâh - reh-aw-yaw' - Reaia","slug":"H7211","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">רְאָיָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Rᵉʼâyâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>reh-aw-yaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Reaia"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>ראיה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>re'âyâh</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>reh-aw-yaw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Reaia or Reaiah = \"Jehovah has seen\" <ol><li>a descendant of Shobal the son of Judah</li><li>a Reubenite, son of Micah and father of Baal</li><li>a progenitor of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H7200\">H7200</a> and <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3070\">H3070</a>, <a href=\"#/H3376\">H3376</a>, <a href=\"#/H4758\">H4758</a>, <a href=\"#/H4759\">H4759</a>, <a href=\"#/H7200\">H7200</a>, <a href=\"#/H7202\">H7202</a>, <a href=\"#/H7203\">H7203</a>, <a href=\"#/H7204\">H7204</a>, <a href=\"#/H7205\">H7205</a>, <a href=\"#/H7206\">H7206</a>, <a href=\"#/H7207\">H7207</a>, <a href=\"#/H7209\">H7209</a>, <a href=\"#/H7210\">H7210</a>, <a href=\"#/H7212\">H7212</a>"}]}